Eisenlord, Appellant, v. Clum, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. September 14, 1892.) Action by John P. Eisenlord against David H. Glum.

Argued before Mayham, P. J., and Putnam and Herrick, JJ.

No opinion. Motion to set aside default granted upon payment of $30, argument fees, and $10, cost of motion, with printing disbursements. All concur. See 2 N. Y. Supp. 125; 19 N. Y. Supp. 1003.
